title: Jabil (JBL) Valuation Check After Raised Outlook and AI-Driven Growth Momentum
text:
Jabil (JBL) Valuation Check After Raised Outlook and AI-Driven Growth Momentum Simply Wall St Thu, 25 December 2025 at 7:08 am GMT+2 2 min read
In this article: JBL
Jabil (JBL) just delivered a fourth quarter that lined up with expectations, but the mix under the hood is what matters, especially the momentum in Intelligent Infrastructure and management’s decision to lift full year revenue and EPS guidance.
See our latest analysis for Jabil.
The upbeat guidance seems to be feeding into an already strong trend, with the stock’s 18.94% 1 month share price return adding to a 64.17% year to date gain and a 5 year total shareholder return of 465.07%. This suggests momentum is still building rather than fading.
If Jabil’s run has you thinking about what else could benefit from similar themes in tech and automation, this is a good moment to explore fast growing stocks with high insider ownership .
With earnings trending higher, a raised revenue outlook, and shares still sitting below the average analyst target, the big question now is whether Jabil remains undervalued or if the market has already priced in its next leg of growth.
Most Popular Narrative Narrative: 9.6% Undervalued With Jabil last closing at 234.49 dollars against a narrative fair value of 259.25 dollars, the story points to more upside if its assumptions hold.
Strong demand in AI related markets, with expected revenue growth of 40% year on year, indicates significant potential to drive future revenue and improve operating margins through an expanded share of high growth technology sectors. The anticipated 1.2 billion dollars in free cash flow generation suggests sound financial health, providing flexibility for share buybacks or strategic investments to further enhance earnings per share growth.
Read the complete narrative.
Curious how steady mid single digit revenue growth, fatter margins, shrinking share count, and a lower future earnings multiple still add up to that valuation? The narrative connects these moving parts into one ambitious earnings path. Want to see exactly how those levers combine to justify the gap to fair value? Read on to unpack the full playbook behind this price target.
Result: Fair Value of $259.25 (UNDERVALUED)
Have a read of the narrative in full and understand what's behind the forecasts.
However, softness in EV and renewable demand, along with tariff uncertainty across key trade corridors, could easily derail those earnings and margin ambitions.
